      "content": "it just feels so cruel, you know? like, why is there no mercy in this? people talk about life being a gift, but when it's just a cycle of agony, it doesn't feel like a gift anymore. it feels like a sentence. sometimes i look at it from the outside and it seems like there's no real wrong in just wanting to be finished with the struggle. like, if there was a way to just opt out of the suffering, wouldn't that be more compassionate than forcing someone to endure this for decades?",
